issue.title: [BUG] Stagging Error with high app size limit
issue.body:
**Describe the bug**
This does put the app into a staging mode which likely causes most of the errors for example you cannot sideload UTM and Dolphin at the same it, it will throw an 'Staging Error' and AltStore does not have this behavior as it refreshes the app's license instead of the entire app itself.

**To Reproduce**
Steps to reproduce the behavior:
1. Install Dolphin with another IPA it will work
2. Install UTM without Dolphin works too with other IPAs

**Expected behavior**
Should not cause the staging issue - could be due to the app size limit.

**iDevice (please complete the following information):**
- iPhone XS 16.1.2
- iPadOS 16.1.1

**Additional context**
Tried it with the stable build and with the recent action - it is still the same. You can try it too.

@JoeMatt @jkcoxson If you could help with the issue it would be highly appreciated.

issue.title: (Instructions) Fix website
issue.body:
This PR removes the CNAME file because as specified in the GitHub Pages documentation, it is not required when deploying from actions.

Instead, this needs to be done in CloudFlare DNS, which should be configured according to the GH documentation (Can also be A record, but CNAME flattening as shown here should also work):
```
sidestore.io    CNAME    sidestore.github.io [CF Proxy/Orange Bubble On]
www.sidestore.io    CNAME    sidestore.github.io [CF Proxy/Orange Bubble On]
```

After that, in the Github Pages settings for this repo, the custom domain needs to be set to `sidestore.io` (I did it with my own subdomain seen in the image for testing), and the source needs to be set to Github Actions
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/56125930/208661447-ef938ff7-f1a3-4934-8693-4551a966d484.png)

@JoeMatt please can you do this (I believe you have access to CloudFlare for the domain) (this should #9)

Also, on this repo can we set the redesign to the default branch and change the `main` branch to a different name? And can we rename the repo to `sidestore.io` or `sidesite` as it makes more sense

issue.title: [Spike] Investigate auto-launching or config'ing wireguard VPN
issue.body:
## Requirements:

1. A way to send config to wireguard from embedded config
2. A way to trigger and/or detect the VPN via URI
3. Detect if wireguard is installed and notify user to download from app store

## Notes:

It seems like it's possible to send a config file, but not a full fledged URI handler for commands.
Also constantly sending the same config with no way of detecting if it's already there first with `canOpen("uri://"` might result in duplicates.

Would probably need to make PR for WireGuard to add some "RPC" methods through URIs.

## Docs:

https://www.macstories.net/ios/a-comprehensive-guide-to-all-120-settings-urls-supported-by-ios-and-ipados-13-1/

https://developer.apple.com/documentation/xcode/defining-a-custom-url-scheme-for-your-app


https://book.hacktricks.xyz/mobile-pentesting/ios-pentesting/ios-custom-uri-handlers-deeplinks-custom-schemes

## Code:

https://github.com/WireGuard/wireguard-apple/blob/9c07693951d570c608d92eccf5d5e6a4d30633d6/Sources/WireGuardApp/UI/iOS/ViewController/MainViewController.swift#L118

https://github.com/WireGuard/wireguard-apple/blob/9c07693951d570c608d92eccf5d5e6a4d30633d6/Sources/WireGuardApp/UI/iOS/AppDelegate.swift#L49

https://github.com/WireGuard/wireguard-apple/blob/9c07693951d570c608d92eccf5d5e6a4d30633d6/Sources/WireGuardApp/UI/iOS/Info.plist#L102
